  "name": "Liver Cancer (HCC) - Diagnosis Code Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find HCC patients via diagnosis codes across primary, broader, and advanced/metastatic SNOMED variants. Synthea distributes patients across these subtypes per the multi-path module.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients with a diagnosis of liver cancer, including primary liver carcinoma, broader malignant liver neoplasms, and metastatic liver malignancies.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find all patients with liver cancer.",
    "broad": "Find all patients diagnosed with any form of liver cancer — including primary hepatocellular carcinoma, the broader 'malignant neoplasm of liver' parent concept, and metastatic malignancies to the liver.",
    "expert": "I need to identify all liver cancer patients. Liver malignancies are coded under multiple SNOMED codes: Primary carcinoma of liver (187769009) is the most specific HCC code, while Malignant neoplasm of liver (93870000) is a broader parent. Metastatic malignant neoplasm to liver (94381002) covers advanced disease. Search Condition resources for these codes."
